<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-09-06T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-09-06T16:00:00-05:00" n="578" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d578">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94111/35: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-09-06T17:00:00-04:00">September 6, 1937—5
                                        p.m.</date></dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>218. Department’s 152, August 16, 2 p.m., and your 461, August 18, 1
                                p.m. Please review this matter in the light of the situation as it
                                now exists and give me by priority radio the benefit of your further
                                views and any comments you may have to offer on the advisability of
                                putting into effect at this stage the initial provision or more of
                                the Act under reference.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>